content_vision: Baby's got a lot of baggage. Fuck it. You know the streets talk. Back in this muthafucka, I spark joints, we can get high. Said my hood like the damn zoo. I remember it well, never gave a fuck about the time, when ya young. And you say we were growing, had to find out the hard way.
structure_suggestion_description: Baby's got a lot of baggage. Fuck it. You know the streets talk. Back in this muthafucka, I spark joints, we can get high. Said my hood like the damn zoo. I remember it well, never gave a fuck about the time, when ya young. And you say we were growing, had to find out the hard way.
text:
Intro:
Baby's got a lot of baggage, but she won't let it bring her down,
she'll keep climbing higher, with her head held high and her crown.

Verse 1:
But I silence the haters, they can't bring me down,
because I'm making moves, while they're just stuck in their small town.
Getting high with my crown on, I reign supreme in my own zone,
flipping off the haters as I claim my throne.
But I keep on rising, no matter how hard they try to bring me down,
'cause I've got my crown and my crew, and we'll always hold our ground.
Getting lost in the music, with my crew by my side,
we'll ride this high all night, embracing this wild ride.

Chorus 1:
High on life, we'll never come down,
baby's got her crown and we'll always wear it proud.
We'll keep climbing higher, reaching for the stars,
we'll keep going wild, living life with no bars.

Verse 2:
I used to hide my pain behind a smile, but now I wear my crown and embrace it with style.
The scars on my skin tell the story of my past, but I'll keep climbing higher, leaving those struggles in the past.
And when the night falls, we'll keep dancing in the street,
because our high is a natural high, can't beat that beat.
But we'll keep living our lives, unapologetic and free,
'cause we're high on love and that's all we'll ever need.
But we'll keep living our lives, unapologetic and free,
'cause we're high on love and that's all we'll ever need.

Chorus 2:
With our heads in the clouds,
and our feet on the ground,
We're living life on our own terms,
raising hell with our endless burns,

Chorus 3:
We'll keep on rising, like smoke from a fire,
never stopping, we'll keep reaching higher and higher.
Our kingdom's risen from the ashes,
and we'll never bow down to their ploys and their clashes.

Bridge:
But I'll keep standing tall, won't let the haters make me fall,
'cause I'm high on my own dreams and that's all.
My highs and lows, make me who I am,
and I'll keep chasing dreams, like a modern-day Peter Pan.
